nodes.title: Global Positive Prompt - to apply to the whole image
Inpainting Prompt - will be applied only to inpainting steps
widgets_values: (leather rainbow pants:1.2), sequin top, towel, rainbows, irridescence

This workflow will inpaint the selected features of the source image and then upscale the source image. Everything is done using iterative mixing sampling to ensure good coherence with the source image. I add some of the latest face matching IPAdapter stuff to further align the face during upscaling.

We use the GroundingDino SegmentAnything node to isolate and mask the subject that we want to inpaint. We also use this node to select some features such as skin to apply via an IPAdapter to help the model align to the subject without hinting at the things we want to paint over. Finally, we select certain things we want to exclude from inpainting, such as the face.

nodes.title: Pad Image to Square for IPAdapter

widgets_values: Reduce the white_level to as low as 50 to brighten dark things that the model is struggling to replace during inpainting, if needed. Otherwise, leave it at 255.

We make three inpainting phases, iteratively refining the inpainting result while the iterative mixing of latents ensures that the inpainting result adheres well to the structure of the original image.
Adjust the stop_blending_at parameter lower if you need to inpaint a bit "harder" at the risk of introducing artifacts like extra limbs.
I recommend lots of steps (60 - 80) and Euler for inpainting.
